            <title>rails dependent destroy on child records in the join table</title>
            <description>i have two join tables in mindbeads.com... one being beads_interests and the other beads_posts&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;to delete dependent records in these tables without unique id per row, i had to build the dependency like this:&lt;br /&gt;has_many :beads_interests, :dependent =&amp;gt; :delete_all&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;instead of &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;:dependent =&amp;gt; :destroy&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;it was throwing an error like this:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NoMethodError: &lt;i&gt;undefined method&lt;/i&gt; `&lt;i&gt;eq' for nil&lt;/i&gt;:NilClass&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/6802601211102647574-7360676882530030608?l=railsonme.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><link>http://railsonme.blogspot.com/2011/02/rails-dependent-destroy-on-child.html</link>
